## Edge cases

- **Regime shifts** — a vol-targeted sizing rule will reduce size into volatility automatically; flag in the report whether this actually preserved capital in 2008 / 2020 / 2022 stress dates. If not, the look-back is too long.
- **Capacity limits binding** — risk engine may cap intended size more often than the strategy author expected; if > 30% of intended trades are size-capped, surface this and recommend `--review` and/or capacity-aware re-sizing.
- **Broker downtime** — kill switch must handle the case where the broker is unreachable; the strategy continues to receive market data and may want to send orders, but cannot. Default: enter "holding-only" mode and notify.
- **Partial fills accumulating** — the risk overlay tracks the divergence between intended book and actual book. If divergence exceeds the configured threshold, the kill switch fires.
- **Correlated kill-switch storm** — if multiple strategies share a kill-switch trigger (e.g., common drawdown event), the simultaneous liquidation can be the cause of further loss. Recommend staggered kill-switches across strategies OR a portfolio-level kill switch above the strategy-level ones.
- **`--kelly-fraction 1.0`** — pure Kelly. AskUserQuestion to confirm; flag in the report status as `Aggressive-Sizing`. Refuse without explicit user confirmation in the same session.

## Dependencies

- `/strategy-design` — spec input.
- `/backtest` — baseline input. Gate: must be Reliable.
- `/paper-trade` — consumer; reads the risk-engine spec and applies the same overlay live.
- **S10 (decision math)** — Kelly, vol-targeting, risk-parity formulas.
- **scikit-learn** — covariance shrinkage estimators (Ledoit-Wolf, etc.) for mean-variance sizing.
- **statsmodels** — drawdown analysis, autocorrelation of returns.
- **`/optimize-decision`** — risk-budget allocation across strategies if more than one is running.

